title: Honeymooner hacked to death in Meghalaya: What wife’s last call to mom-in-law hinted at

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru won their first IPL title as Allu Arjun's son, Allu Ayaan, celebrated emotionally. He poured water on himself and expressed his love for Virat Kohli and was relieved that he no longer had to use the phrase 'Ee Saala Cup Lollipop'. Virat Kohli too, was overcome with emotion as he got his hands on the trophy after an 18-year wait.
title: 'I cannot say Ee Sala Cup Lollipop': Allu Arjun's son following RCB's win

description: ITR Filing FY 2024-25: The Income Tax Department has enabled online ITR filing for FY 2024-25 (AY 2025-26) via incometax.gov.in, initially supporting ITR-1 and ITR-4 forms. These forms are for individuals with income up to Rs 50 lakh from specific sources.

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: British pop sensation Jessie J, 37, has revealed her diagnosis of early-stage breast cancer. The 'Who You Are' singer shared the news on Instagram, admitting her initial hesitation. Diagnosed just before her single 'No Secrets' release, she's undergone tests and plans surgery post Summertime Ball.
title: Singer Jessie J diagnosed with breast cancer

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Mani Ratnam and Kamal Haasan reunite after 36 years with 'Thug Life,' featuring music by A.R. Rahman and a stellar cast. Early reviews are positive, calling it a potential cult classic, but controversy arises in Karnataka over Kamal Haasan's past remarks about the Kannada language. Despite the challenges, the film is generating significant buzz and high ticket sales.
title: ‘Thug Life’ early review: Kamal Haasan & Mani Ratnam's film is a 'cult classic'

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Indian authorities are investigating YouTubers Jyoti Malhotra and Jasbir Singh for alleged espionage linked to Pakistani intelligence. Malhotra, known as "Travel with Jo," is accused of sharing sensitive information and maintaining contact with Pakistani officials via encrypted apps.
title: Watch: When 'spy' YouTubers Jyoti Malhotra and Jasbir Singh were together in Pakistan

author: TNN
description: In Karnataka's Chikkaballapura district, a shocking incident has unfolded where Mefuz, a 55-year-old merchant and father of a cleric, has been arrested. He is accused of raping a six-year-old girl inside a mosque.
title: 6-year-old lured with chocolates, raped inside mosque in Karnataka's Chikkaballapura

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru secured their first IPL title, defeating Punjab Kings in a thrilling final. Virat Kohli, overwhelmed with emotion, dedicated the victory to his family, especially his wife Anushka Sharma. He acknowledged their unwavering support throughout his 18-year journey with the team. Kohli emphasised his commitment to contributing to the team's success, both on and off the field.
title: 'Anushka, my mum, my brother …': Kohli fights back tears in an emotional interview

author: PRATYUSH RAJ
description: Virat Kohli’s teary moment at Ahmedabad marked the end of an 18-year IPL title drought for RCB. Battling years of criticism, self-doubt, and heartbreak, Kohli rose like a phoenix to finally achieve his elusive dream. Though a subdued celebration followed, it might just be a start of something special.
title: From tears to triumph: Virat Kohli’s emotional IPL coronation after 18-year wait

author: JAIKRISHNAN NAIR
description: Aswathy Ashok posted a video of her son Shanku requesting biryani instead of upma. The video went viral. Kerala's Women and Child Development Minister Veena George noticed it. She promised to consider the request. George kept her word and included egg biryani in the revised anganwadi menu. The new menu also includes pulao.
title: ‘I don’t want upma’: 4-year-old Shanku’s viral demand video gets biryani added to anganwadi menu in Kerala

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Kamal Haasan's 'Thug Life' is leading in advance bookings, grossing ₹3.42 crore, surpassing Akshay Kumar's 'Housefull 5' which garnered ₹2.15 crore. 'Thug Life' dominates in Tamil Nadu, fueled by Kamal Haasan's comeback and Mani Ratnam's direction. Despite 'Housefull 5' appealing to a broader audience, 'Thug Life' is poised to potentially steal the box office spotlight.
title: Kamal Haasan’s Thug Life outpaces Akshay Kumar’s Housefull 5 in advance bookings

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Bilawal Bhutto-Zardari expressed Pakistan's willingness to cooperate with India in combating terrorism, advocating for a dispute resolution mechanism and joint efforts between intelligence agencies. Shashi Tharoor noted the heightened interest due to the simultaneous presence of Indian and Pakistani delegations in the US.
title: Shift in tone? Bilawal seeks intel cooperation with India; underlines terror threat

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Following widespread condemnation, the Trump administration reversed its decision to revoke the legal status of Sofia Vargas, a four-year-old Mexican girl receiving life-saving treatment in the US. The family, who arrived in 2023, faced deportation after their humanitarian parole was terminated. Doctors warned Sofia would die without continued specialized care.
title: Trump admin reverses deportation order of four-year-old child

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Bilawal Bhutto-Zardari alleged the demonization of Muslims in India at a UN press conference, a claim challenged by a journalist. The journalist pointed out that Muslim military officers, including Colonel Sofiya Qureshi, were involved in briefings regarding India's counter-terror operations following the Pahalgam attack. Operation Sindoor led to cross-border clashes until a ceasefire was established.
title: Watch: Bilawal Bhutto’s remark on Muslims in India hits a wall; reporter invokes Op Sindoor

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold price prediction today: Gold prices are experiencing a volatile week, consolidating below April's record highs amid geopolitical tensions and fluctuating safe-haven demand. Concerns over US-China trade relations and potential tariff increases added to market uncertainty. Despite dovish signals from the Federal Reserve, rate cut probabilities remain delayed, influencing bullion prices.

description: Punjab Police's SSOC has exposed a terror-linked espionage network allegedly backed by Pakistan. Jasbir Singh, a YouTuber, is accused of maintaining contact with PIOs suspected of working for Pakistani handlers, including a previously arrested spy and an expelled Pakistani official. Singh's travels to Pakistan and interactions with Pakistani officials are under investigation, with seized devices undergoing forensic analysis.
title: Espionage case: After Jyoti Malhotra, another YouTuber under lens; travelled to Pakistan thrice

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU) has decided to replace 'Kulpati' with 'Kulguru' for its vice-chancellor on degree certificates and academic records, a decision made during an Executive Council meeting in April. The move aims for a more inclusive and gender-neutral title, aligning with similar changes in Madhya Pradesh and Rajasthan.
title: Gender-neutral shift: JNU vice-chancellor to be called 'Kulguru' instead of 'Kulpati'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Virat Kohli's 18-year quest for an IPL title concluded triumphantly as Royal Challengers Bengaluru defeated Punjab Kings in a thrilling final. Kohli's crucial 43 runs contributed significantly to RCB's victory. Anand Mahindra lauded Kohli's unwavering loyalty, stating it carves legacies. Mahindra highlighted Kohli's dedication to RCB, emphasising that the stars finally aligned after years of anticipation.

author: DEVANSHI MEHTA
description: Recent murders of three young women in Delhi, Komal, Vijaylaxmi, and Mehek Jain, highlight the dangers of possessive relationships. Fueled by jealousy and control, the perpetrators allegedly monitored their girlfriends on social media, particularly Instagram. Experts attribute this violence to deep-seated insecurities, unrealistic expectations, and the normalization of toxic behaviors, further exacerbated by social media's influence.
title: Toxic love kills: 3 young women murdered by possessive partners in Delhi

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: In Delhi, a sextortion gang led by Jahid allegedly used AI and social media to blackmail vulnerable individuals. Jayshree lured victims, while others impersonated police. Another call center, managed by Ujjawal Pandey and Gaurav Barua, offered fake loans, extracting fees before cutting contact. Telecallers like Akshita, Dimple, and Pinki, under Dilshad Ali, posed as loan representatives, deceiving customers.
title: AI cyber fraud: Inside Delhi’s ‘telecaller trap’; fraud kits, dummy a/cs powered racket

author: ADVITYA BAHL
description: In Noida's Sector 53, a social media feud escalated into a violent assault on Monday. Saurabh Yadav and his brother were attacked by a group, including Akash and Aman Awana, allegedly linked to illegal activities. The brothers were beaten, and Saurabh was nearly run over by a Thar.
title: Bricks, blades & Thar: Instagram feud turns bloody in Noida, youth run over by SUV

author: KALYAN DAS
description: In Dehradun's Premnagar, BJP's former mandal president, Rohit Negi, was fatally shot late Tuesday night. The attack occurred as Negi and his friends were returning home after dinner. Accused Azhar Tyagi from Muzaffarnagar, along with an accomplice, ambushed Negi's car following a heated phone argument allegedly sparked by a friend's relationship.
title: Ex-BJP mandal chief shot dead in Dehradun after quarrel over 'friend's relationship with girl'

description: Indore honeymooner Raja Raghuvanshi was murdered with a machete near Weisawdong falls in Sohra, police confirmed after his body was discovered. The family suspects foul play and demands a CBI investigation, alleging crucial search efforts were initially ignored.

Despite this, Haasan has garnered significant support, with fans defending his statements as rooted in linguistic history and not intended as an insult.

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US president Trump has signed an order doubling tariffs on imported steel and aluminum to 50%, citing national security concerns and aiming to protect domestic industries from foreign dumping. While tariffs on UK imports remain at 25%, the hike targets other partners, prompting warnings of retaliation from the European Union and Mexico seeking an exemption, adding pressure to ongoing trade talks.

author: ABHAY
description: Mehak Jain, a bright 19-year-old student, was murdered by her boyfriend, Arshkrit Singh, just days before her birthday. Singh, suspicious and controlling, harassed Jain, even stalking her Korean classes. He created fake social media profiles to monitor her interactions. On Sunday, an argument in a park escalated, leading Singh to attack Jain with petrol and a knife.
title: How ‘couldn’t let go’ led to DU student’s murder by boyfriend days before her 19th bday

author: DHANANJAY.MAHAPATRA
description: The Supreme Court has dismissed rape charges against a man, citing the woman's "aggressive sexual behaviour" and manipulative tendencies. Justices Nath and Mehta referenced social media chats where the woman, known as 'Muffin,' admitted to manipulation and targeting men for personal gain, including seeking a green card.
title: SC quashes rape charges: Man refuses to marry woman over ‘aggressive sexual nature’

author: RASHMI DROLIA
description: In Chhattisgarh's Bilaspur, a speeding Innova crashed, killing a businessman. The driver opened the door to spit gutkha, losing control. The vehicle flipped, hitting other vehicles. Jackie Gehi died on the spot. Akash Chandani and Pankaj Chhabra were critically injured. The accident occurred on the Bilaspur-Raipur highway. Police arrived and sealed off the area. The injured were hospitalized.
title: Chhattisgarh: Driver opens door at 100kmph to spit gutka, man dies in crash; 3 hurt

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Three Indian nationals from Punjab, who had been missing in Iran since May 1 while en route to Australia with promises of lucrative jobs, have been rescued by Tehran police. The men were freed following a police operation in south Tehran's Varamin against their hostage-takers.
title: Found & released: 3 Indians missing in Iran rescued by cops in Tehran; all you need to know

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Targeting arm toning is a common fitness goal, especially during summer. This article suggests incorporating dumbbell exercises into your routine to build muscle and reduce arm fat. It outlines five simple exercises that can be performed at home, including bicep curls, plié V raises, arm circles, tricep kickbacks, and overhead dumbbell presses, to help achieve toned arms.
title: How to reduce arm fat: 5 easy dumbbell exercises that can be done at home

description: RCB head coach Andy Flower revealed that the IPL 2025 suspension, gave injured players like Rajat Patidar and Josh Hazlewood vital recovery time. description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru won their first IPL title, defeating Punjab Kings in a thrilling final. Rajat Patidar-led RCB defended a score of 190 as Virat Kohli's emotional reaction became a highlight. The No 18 and his teammates bust out some moves after the thrilling win upon reaching the team hotel.

Virat Kohli, overwhelmed with emotion, symbolised the end of a long wait as RCB finally achieved victory, celebrated by fellow IPL teams.

description: In Raigad's Pen taluka, Suresh Dore, a 40-year-old man from an Adivasi hamlet, was arrested for the murder of his one-year-old daughter. Irritated by her crying, Dore fatally injured her by banging her head on the floor.

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) ended their 18-year wait for an IPL title, defeating Punjab Kings in a thrilling final. description: ArduPilot, an open-source software initially created for hobbyist drones, has reportedly been used in a Ukrainian attack that destroyed a portion of Russia's strategic bomber fleet. The software's creators expressed surprise at its military application, as it was originally designed for peaceful purposes like search and rescue and autonomous vehicles.
